e long term. \nCollisions involving non-maneuverable upper stages and spacecraft are predicted to become \nthe dominant source of new debris. Currently, the mean time interval between catastrophic \ncollisions of cataloged objects in low Earth orbit is approximately 5 to 9 years [1]. The \nassociated frequency of collisions will increase as time progresses if no active measures are \nundertaken to counteract this trend. \nRemediation of the near-Earth space environment involves the direct removal of space debris, \nalso known as active debris removal or ADR. Several IADC member agencies, as well as other", "embedding": [-0.048415184020996094, -0.011885354295372963, 0.03958964720368385, -0.04773681238293648, 0.015026248060166836, 0.0041933245956897736, 0.0186464823782444, -0.011042803525924683, 0.0017851850716397166, -0.01938847079873085, 0.0664234459400177, -0.012052550911903381, 0.01220148429274559, 0.0344715341925621, -0.08526211231946945, -0.007304934784770012, 0.005088671110570431, -0.003018927527591586, 0.022408898919820786, -0.005831621587276459, 0.03755011409521103, -0.0006723944679833949, 0.005945637356489897, 0.013328513130545616, -0.009539062157273293, 0.08462194353342056, -0.04027917608618736, -0.06735417991876602, -0.032611966133117676, -0.2452460676431656, -0.03680405393242836, -0.06628219038248062, -0.0030002291314303875, -0.0017034246120601892, -0.05720767378807068, -0.003621767507866025, -0.017376137897372246, 0.006811350118368864, -0.005404029041528702, 0.018268194049596786, 0.034782279282808304, 0.040469691157341, 0.02759585715830326, -0.02999376505613327, -0.035575445741415024, 0.004952626768499613, 0.023462243378162384, -0.09163282066583633, -0.016859114170074463, 0.020747605711221695, 0.015981357544660568, -0.029164770618081093, 0.0042005800642073154, 0.06101718172430992, -0.012548670172691345, -0.017380286008119583, 0.015154884196817875, -0.01626402512192726, 0.04508880525827408, 0.014818079769611359, 0.0061479974538087845, -0.04201424494385719